5464
5465// Return true is this is a SETCC node or a strict version of it.
5466static inline bool isSETCCOp(unsigned Opcode) {
5467 switch (Opcode) {
5468 case ISD::SETCC:
5469 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCC:
5470 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS:
5471 return true;
5472 }
5473 return false;
5474}
5475
5476// Return true if this is a node that could have two SETCCs as operands.
5477static inline bool isLogicalMaskOp(unsigned Opcode) {
5478 switch (Opcode) {
5479 case ISD::AND:
5480 case ISD::OR:
5481 case ISD::XOR:
5482 return true;
5483 }
5484 return false;
5485}
5486
5487// If N is a SETCC or a strict variant of it, return the type
5488// of the compare operands.
5489static inline EVT getSETCCOperandType(SDValue N) {
5490 unsigned OpNo = N->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0;
5491 return N->getOperand(OpNo).getValueType();
5492}
5493
5494// This is used just for the assert in convertMask(). Check that this either
5495// a SETCC or a previously handled SETCC by convertMask().
5496#ifndef NDEBUG
5497static inline bool isSETCCorConvertedSETCC(SDValue N) {
5498 if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR)
5499 N = N.getOperand(0);
5500 else if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS) {
5501 for (unsigned i = 1; i < N->getNumOperands(); ++i)
5502 if (!N->getOperand(i)->isUndef())
5503 return false;
5504 N = N.getOperand(0);
5505 }
5506
5507 if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE)
5508 N = N.getOperand(0);
5509 else if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND)
5510 N = N.getOperand(0);
5511
5512 if (isLogicalMaskOp(N.getOpcode()))
5513 return isSETCCorConvertedSETCC(N.getOperand(0)) &&
5514 isSETCCorConvertedSETCC(N.getOperand(1));
5515
5516 return (isSETCCOp(N.getOpcode()) ||
5517 ISD::isBuildVectorOfConstantSDNodes(N.getNode()));
5518}
5519#endif
5520
5521// Return a mask of vector type MaskVT to replace InMask. Also adjust MaskVT
5522// to ToMaskVT if needed with vector extension or truncation.
5523SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::convertMask(SDValue InMask, EVT MaskVT,
5524 EVT ToMaskVT) {
5525 // Currently a SETCC or a AND/OR/XOR with two SETCCs are handled.
5526 // FIXME: This code seems to be too restrictive, we might consider
5527 // generalizing it or dropping it.
5528 assert(isSETCCorConvertedSETCC(InMask) && "Unexpected mask argument.");
5529
5530 // Make a new Mask node, with a legal result VT.
5531 SDValue Mask;
5532 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Ops;
5533 for (unsigned i = 0, e = InMask->getNumOperands(); i < e; ++i)
5534 Ops.push_back(InMask->getOperand(i));
5535 if (InMask->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
5536 Mask = DAG.getNode(InMask->getOpcode(), SDLoc(InMask),
5537 { MaskVT, MVT::Other }, Ops);
5538 ReplaceValueWith(InMask.getValue(1), Mask.getValue(1));
5539 }
5540 else
5541 Mask = DAG.getNode(InMask->getOpcode(), SDLoc(InMask), MaskVT, Ops);
5542
5543 // If MaskVT has smaller or bigger elements than ToMaskVT, a vector sign
5544 // extend or truncate is needed.
5545 LLVMContext &Ctx = *DAG.getContext();
5546 unsigned MaskScalarBits = MaskVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
5547 unsigned ToMaskScalBits = ToMaskVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
5548 if (MaskScalarBits < ToMaskScalBits) {
5549 EVT ExtVT = EVT::getVectorVT(Ctx, ToMaskVT.getVectorElementType(),
5550 MaskVT.getVectorNumElements());
5551 Mask = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, SDLoc(Mask), ExtVT, Mask);
5552 } else if (MaskScalarBits > ToMaskScalBits) {
5553 EVT TruncVT = EVT::getVectorVT(Ctx, ToMaskVT.getVectorElementType(),
5554 MaskVT.getVectorNumElements());
5555 Mask = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SDLoc(Mask), TruncVT, Mask);
5556 }
5557
5558 assert(Mask->getValueType(0).getScalarSizeInBits() ==
5559 ToMaskVT.getScalarSizeInBits() &&
5560 "Mask should have the right element size by now.");
5561
5562 // Adjust Mask to the right number of elements.
5563 unsigned CurrMaskNumEls = Mask->getValueType(0).getVectorNumElements();
5564 if (CurrMaskNumEls > ToMaskVT.getVectorNumElements()) {
5565 SDValue ZeroIdx = DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, SDLoc(Mask));
5566 Mask = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, SDLoc(Mask), ToMaskVT, Mask,
5567 ZeroIdx);
5568 } else if (CurrMaskNumEls < ToMaskVT.getVectorNumElements()) {
5569 unsigned NumSubVecs = (ToMaskVT.getVectorNumElements() / CurrMaskNumEls);
5570 EVT SubVT = Mask->getValueType(0);
5571 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> SubOps(NumSubVecs, DAG.getUNDEF(SubVT));
5572 SubOps[0] = Mask;
5573 Mask = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, SDLoc(Mask), ToMaskVT, SubOps);
5574 }
5575
5576 assert((Mask->getValueType(0) == ToMaskVT) &&
5577 "A mask of ToMaskVT should have been produced by now.");
5578
5579 return Mask;
5580}
5581
5582// This method tries to handle some special cases for the vselect mask
5583// and if needed adjusting the mask vector type to match that of the VSELECT.
5584// Without it, many cases end up with scalarization of the SETCC, with many
5585// unnecessary instructions.
5586SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVSELECTMask(SDNode *N) {
5587 LLVMContext &Ctx = *DAG.getContext();
5588 SDValue Cond = N->getOperand(0);
5589
5590 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::VSELECT)
5591 return SDValue();
5592
5593 if (!isSETCCOp(Cond->getOpcode()) && !isLogicalMaskOp(Cond->getOpcode()))
5594 return SDValue();
5595
5596 // If this is a splitted VSELECT that was previously already handled, do
5597 // nothing.
5598 EVT CondVT = Cond->getValueType(0);
5599 if (CondVT.getScalarSizeInBits() != 1)
5600 return SDValue();
5601
5602 EVT VSelVT = N->getValueType(0);
5603
5604 // This method can't handle scalable vector types.
5605 // FIXME: This support could be added in the future.
5606 if (VSelVT.isScalableVector())
5607 return SDValue();
5608
5609 // Only handle vector types which are a power of 2.
5610 if (!isPowerOf2_64(VSelVT.getSizeInBits()))
5611 return SDValue();
5612
5613 // Don't touch if this will be scalarized.
5614 EVT FinalVT = VSelVT;
5615 while (getTypeAction(FinalVT) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
5616 FinalVT = FinalVT.getHalfNumVectorElementsVT(Ctx);
5617
5618 if (FinalVT.getVectorNumElements() == 1)
5619 return SDValue();
5620
5621 // If there is support for an i1 vector mask, don't touch.
5622 if (isSETCCOp(Cond.getOpcode())) {
5623 EVT SetCCOpVT = getSETCCOperandType(Cond);
5624 while (TLI.getTypeAction(Ctx, SetCCOpVT) != TargetLowering::TypeLegal)
5625 SetCCOpVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(Ctx, SetCCOpVT);
5626 EVT SetCCResVT = getSetCCResultType(SetCCOpVT);
5627 if (SetCCResVT.getScalarSizeInBits() == 1)
5628 return SDValue();
5629 } else if (CondVT.getScalarType() == MVT::i1) {
5630 // If there is support for an i1 vector mask (or only scalar i1 conditions),
5631 // don't touch.
5632 while (TLI.getTypeAction(Ctx, CondVT) != TargetLowering::TypeLegal)
5633 CondVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(Ctx, CondVT);
5634
5635 if (CondVT.getScalarType() == MVT::i1)
5636 return SDValue();
5637 }
5638
5639 // Widen the vselect result type if needed.
5640 if (getTypeAction(VSelVT) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector)
5641 VSelVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(Ctx, VSelVT);
5642
5643 // The mask of the VSELECT should have integer elements.
5644 EVT ToMaskVT = VSelVT;
5645 if (!ToMaskVT.getScalarType().isInteger())
5646 ToMaskVT = ToMaskVT.changeVectorElementTypeToInteger();
5647
5648 SDValue Mask;
5649 if (isSETCCOp(Cond->getOpcode())) {
5650 EVT MaskVT = getSetCCResultType(getSETCCOperandType(Cond));
5651 Mask = convertMask(Cond, MaskVT, ToMaskVT);
5652 } else if (isLogicalMaskOp(Cond->getOpcode()) &&
5653 isSETCCOp(Cond->getOperand(0).getOpcode()) &&
5654 isSETCCOp(Cond->getOperand(1).getOpcode())) {
5655 // Cond is (AND/OR/XOR (SETCC, SETCC))
5656 SDValue SETCC0 = Cond->getOperand(0);
5657 SDValue SETCC1 = Cond->getOperand(1);
5658 EVT VT0 = getSetCCResultType(getSETCCOperandType(SETCC0));
5659 EVT VT1 = getSetCCResultType(getSETCCOperandType(SETCC1));
5660 unsigned ScalarBits0 = VT0.getScalarSizeInBits();
5661 unsigned ScalarBits1 = VT1.getScalarSizeInBits();
5662 unsigned ScalarBits_ToMask = ToMaskVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
5663 EVT MaskVT;
5664 // If the two SETCCs have different VTs, either extend/truncate one of
5665 // them to the other "towards" ToMaskVT, or truncate one and extend the
5666 // other to ToMaskVT.
5667 if (ScalarBits0 != ScalarBits1) {
5668 EVT NarrowVT = ((ScalarBits0 < ScalarBits1) ? VT0 : VT1);
5669 EVT WideVT = ((NarrowVT == VT0) ? VT1 : VT0);
5670 if (ScalarBits_ToMask >= WideVT.getScalarSizeInBits())
5671 MaskVT = WideVT;
5672 else if (ScalarBits_ToMask <= NarrowVT.getScalarSizeInBits())
5673 MaskVT = NarrowVT;
5674 else
5675 MaskVT = ToMaskVT;
5676 } else
5677 // If the two SETCCs have the same VT, don't change it.
5678 MaskVT = VT0;
5679
5680 // Make new SETCCs and logical nodes.
5681 SETCC0 = convertMask(SETCC0, VT0, MaskVT);
5682 SETCC1 = convertMask(SETCC1, VT1, MaskVT);
5683 Cond = DAG.getNode(Cond->getOpcode(), SDLoc(Cond), MaskVT, SETCC0, SETCC1);
5684
5685 // Convert the logical op for VSELECT if needed.
5686 Mask = convertMask(Cond, MaskVT, ToMaskVT);
5687 } else
5688 return SDValue();
5689
5690 return Mask;
5691}
5692
5693SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_Select(SDNode *N) {
5694 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
5695 ElementCount WidenEC = WidenVT.getVectorElementCount();
5696
5697 SDValue Cond1 = N->getOperand(0);
5698 EVT CondVT = Cond1.getValueType();
5699 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
5700 if (CondVT.isVector()) {
5701 if (SDValue WideCond = WidenVSELECTMask(N)) {
5702 SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
5703 SDValue InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(2));
5704 assert(InOp1.getValueType() == WidenVT && InOp2.getValueType() == WidenVT);
5705 return DAG.getNode(Opcode, SDLoc(N), WidenVT, WideCond, InOp1, InOp2);
5706 }
5707
5708 EVT CondEltVT = CondVT.getVectorElementType();
5709 EVT CondWidenVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), CondEltVT, WidenEC);
5710 if (getTypeAction(CondVT) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector)
5711 Cond1 = GetWidenedVector(Cond1);
5712
5713 // If we have to split the condition there is no point in widening the
5714 // select. This would result in an cycle of widening the select ->
5715 // widening the condition operand -> splitting the condition operand ->
5716 // splitting the select -> widening the select. Instead split this select
5717 // further and widen the resulting type.
5718 if (getTypeAction(CondVT) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector) {
5719 SDValue SplitSelect = SplitVecOp_VSELECT(N, 0);
5720 SDValue Res = ModifyToType(SplitSelect, WidenVT);
5721 return Res;
5722 }
5723
5724 if (Cond1.getValueType() != CondWidenVT)
5725 Cond1 = ModifyToType(Cond1, CondWidenVT);
5726 }
5727
5728 SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
5729 SDValue InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(2));
5730 assert(InOp1.getValueType() == WidenVT && InOp2.getValueType() == WidenVT);
5731 if (Opcode == ISD::VP_SELECT || Opcode == ISD::VP_MERGE)
5732 return DAG.getNode(Opcode, SDLoc(N), WidenVT, Cond1, InOp1, InOp2,
5733 N->getOperand(3));
5734 return DAG.getNode(Opcode, SDLoc(N), WidenVT, Cond1, InOp1, InOp2);
5735}
5736
5737SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_SELECT_CC(SDNode *N) {
5738 SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(2));
5739 SDValue InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(3));
5740 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT_CC, SDLoc(N),
5741 InOp1.getValueType(), N->getOperand(0),
5742 N->getOperand(1), InOp1, InOp2, N->getOperand(4));
5743}
5744
5745SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_UNDEF(SDNode *N) {
5746 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
5747 return DAG.getUNDEF(WidenVT);
5748}
5749
5750SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_VECTOR_SHUFFLE(ShuffleVectorSDNode *N) {
5751 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
5752 SDLoc dl(N);
5753
5754 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
5755 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
5756 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
5757
5758 SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
5759 SDValue InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
5760
5761 // Adjust mask based on new input vector length.
5762 SmallVector<int, 16> NewMask;
5763 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
5764 int Idx = N->getMaskElt(i);
5765 if (Idx < (int)NumElts)
5766 NewMask.push_back(Idx);
5767 else
5768 NewMask.push_back(Idx - NumElts + WidenNumElts);
5769 }
5770 for (unsigned i = NumElts; i != WidenNumElts; ++i)
5771 NewMask.push_back(-1);
5772 return DAG.getVectorShuffle(WidenVT, dl, InOp1, InOp2, NewMask);
5773}
5774
5775SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_VECTOR_REVERSE(SDNode *N) {
5776 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
5777 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
5778 SDLoc dl(N);
5779
5780 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
5781 SDValue OpValue = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
5782 assert(WidenVT == OpValue.getValueType() && "Unexpected widened vector type");
5783
5784 SDValue ReverseVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::VECTOR_REVERSE, dl, WidenVT, OpValue);
5785 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
5786 unsigned VTNumElts = VT.getVectorMinNumElements();
5787 unsigned IdxVal = WidenNumElts - VTNumElts;
5788
5789 if (VT.isScalableVector()) {
5790 // Try to split the 'Widen ReverseVal' into smaller extracts and concat the
5791 // results together, e.g.(nxv6i64 -> nxv8i64)
5792 // nxv8i64 vector_reverse
5793 // <->
5794 // nxv8i64 concat(
5795 // nxv2i64 extract_subvector(nxv8i64, 2)
5796 // nxv2i64 extract_subvector(nxv8i64, 4)
5797 // nxv2i64 extract_subvector(nxv8i64, 6)
5798 // nxv2i64 undef)
5799
5800 unsigned GCD = std::gcd(VTNumElts, WidenNumElts);
5801 EVT PartVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), EltVT,
5802 ElementCount::getScalable(GCD));
5803 assert((IdxVal % GCD) == 0 && "Expected Idx to be a multiple of the broken "
5804 "down type's element count");
5805 SmallVector<SDValue> Parts;
5806 unsigned i = 0;
5807 for (; i < VTNumElts / GCD; ++i)
5808 Parts.push_back(
5809 DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, PartVT, ReverseVal,
5810 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(IdxVal + i * GCD, dl)));
5811 for (; i < WidenNumElts / GCD; ++i)
5812 Parts.push_back(DAG.getUNDEF(PartVT));
5813
5814 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, WidenVT, Parts);
5815 }
5816
5817 // Use VECTOR_SHUFFLE to combine new vector from 'ReverseVal' for
5818 // fixed-vectors.
5819 SmallVector<int, 16> Mask;
5820 for (unsigned i = 0; i != VTNumElts; ++i) {
5821 Mask.push_back(IdxVal + i);
5822 }
5823 for (unsigned i = VTNumElts; i != WidenNumElts; ++i)
5824 Mask.push_back(-1);
5825
5826 return DAG.getVectorShuffle(WidenVT, dl, ReverseVal, DAG.getUNDEF(WidenVT),
5827 Mask);
5828}
5829
5830SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_SETCC(SDNode *N) {
5831 assert(N->getValueType(0).isVector() &&
5832 N->getOperand(0).getValueType().isVector() &&
5833 "Operands must be vectors");
5834 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
5835 ElementCount WidenEC = WidenVT.getVectorElementCount();
5836
5837 SDValue InOp1 = N->getOperand(0);
5838 EVT InVT = InOp1.getValueType();
5839 assert(InVT.isVector() && "can not widen non-vector type");
5840 EVT WidenInVT =
5841 EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), InVT.getVectorElementType(), WidenEC);
5842
5843 // The input and output types often differ here, and it could be that while
5844 // we'd prefer to widen the result type, the input operands have been split.
5845 // In this case, we also need to split the result of this node as well.
5846 if (getTypeAction(InVT) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector) {
5847 SDValue SplitVSetCC = SplitVecOp_VSETCC(N);
5848 SDValue Res = ModifyToType(SplitVSetCC, WidenVT);
5849 return Res;
5850 }
5851
5852 // If the inputs also widen, handle them directly. Otherwise widen by hand.
5853 SDValue InOp2 = N->getOperand(1);
5854 if (getTypeAction(InVT) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector) {
5855 InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(InOp1);
5856 InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(InOp2);
5857 } else {
5858 InOp1 = DAG.WidenVector(InOp1, SDLoc(N));
5859 InOp2 = DAG.WidenVector(InOp2, SDLoc(N));
5860 }
5861
5862 // Assume that the input and output will be widen appropriately. If not,
5863 // we will have to unroll it at some point.
5864 assert(InOp1.getValueType() == WidenInVT &&
5865 InOp2.getValueType() == WidenInVT &&
5866 "Input not widened to expected type!");
5867 (void)WidenInVT;
5868 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::VP_SETCC) {
5869 SDValue Mask =
5870 GetWidenedMask(N->getOperand(3), WidenVT.getVectorElementCount());
5871 return DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SETCC, SDLoc(N), WidenVT, InOp1, InOp2,
5872 N->getOperand(2), Mask, N->getOperand(4));
5873 }
5874 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, SDLoc(N), WidenVT, InOp1, InOp2,
5875 N->getOperand(2));
5876}
5877
5878SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_STRICT_FSETCC(SDNode *N) {
5879 assert(N->getValueType(0).isVector() &&
5880 N->getOperand(1).getValueType().isVector() &&
5881 "Operands must be vectors");
5882 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
5883 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
5884 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
5885 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
5886 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
5887
5888 SDLoc dl(N);
5889 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
5890 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(1);
5891 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(2);
5892 SDValue CC = N->getOperand(3);
5893 EVT TmpEltVT = LHS.getValueType().getVectorElementType();
5894
5895 // Fully unroll and reassemble.
5896 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Scalars(WidenNumElts, DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT));
5897 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Chains(NumElts);
5898 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
5899 SDValue LHSElem = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, TmpEltVT, LHS,
5900 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
5901 SDValue RHSElem = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, TmpEltVT, RHS,
5902 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
5903
5904 Scalars[i] = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, {MVT::i1, MVT::Other},
5905 {Chain, LHSElem, RHSElem, CC});
5906 Chains[i] = Scalars[i].getValue(1);
5907 Scalars[i] = DAG.getSelect(dl, EltVT, Scalars[i],
5908 DAG.getBoolConstant(true, dl, EltVT, VT),
5909 DAG.getBoolConstant(false, dl, EltVT, VT));
5910 }
5911
5912 SDValue NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Chains);
5913 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), NewChain);
5914
5915 return DAG.getBuildVector(WidenVT, dl, Scalars);
5916}
5917
5918//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5919// Widen Vector Operand
5920//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5921bool DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVectorOperand(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
5922 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Widen node operand " << OpNo << ": "; N->dump(&DAG);
5923 dbgs() << "\n");
5924 SDValue Res = SDValue();
5925
5926 // See if the target wants to custom widen this node.
5927 if (CustomLowerNode(N, N->getOperand(OpNo).getValueType(), false))
5928 return false;
5929
5930 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
5931 default:
5932#ifndef NDEBUG
5933 dbgs() << "WidenVectorOperand op #" << OpNo << ": ";
5934 N->dump(&DAG);
5935 dbgs() << "\n";
5936#endif
5937 report_fatal_error("Do not know how to widen this operator's operand!");
5938
5939 case ISD::BITCAST: Res = WidenVecOp_BITCAST(N); break;
5940 case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: Res = WidenVecOp_CONCAT_VECTORS(N); break;
5941 case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR: Res = WidenVecOp_INSERT_SUBVECTOR(N); break;
5942 case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: Res = WidenVecOp_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(N); break;
5943 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: Res = WidenVecOp_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(N); break;
5944 case ISD::STORE: Res = WidenVecOp_STORE(N); break;
5945 case ISD::VP_STORE: Res = WidenVecOp_VP_STORE(N, OpNo); break;
5946 case ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_STORE:
5947 Res = WidenVecOp_VP_STRIDED_STORE(N, OpNo);
5948 break;
5949 case ISD::MSTORE: Res = WidenVecOp_MSTORE(N, OpNo); break;
5950 case ISD::MGATHER: Res = WidenVecOp_MGATHER(N, OpNo); break;
5951 case ISD::MSCATTER: Res = WidenVecOp_MSCATTER(N, OpNo); break;
5952 case ISD::VP_SCATTER: Res = WidenVecOp_VP_SCATTER(N, OpNo); break;
5953 case ISD::SETCC: Res = WidenVecOp_SETCC(N); break;
5954 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCC:
5955 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS: Res = WidenVecOp_STRICT_FSETCC(N); break;
5956 case ISD::VSELECT: Res = WidenVecOp_VSELECT(N); break;
5957 case ISD::FLDEXP:
5958 case ISD::FCOPYSIGN: Res = WidenVecOp_UnrollVectorOp(N); break;
5959 case ISD::IS_FPCLASS: Res = WidenVecOp_IS_FPCLASS(N); break;
5960
5961 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
5962 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
5963 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
5964 Res = WidenVecOp_EXTEND(N);
5965 break;
5966
5967 case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
5968 case ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND:
5969 case ISD::FP_ROUND:
5970 case ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND:
5971 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
5972 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT:
5973 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
5974 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT:
5975 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
5976 case ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP:
5977 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
5978 case ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP:
5979 case ISD::TRUNCATE:
5980 Res = WidenVecOp_Convert(N);
5981 break;
5982
5983 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT:
5984 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT:
5985 Res = WidenVecOp_FP_TO_XINT_SAT(N);
5986 break;
5987
5988 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FADD:
5989 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMUL:
5990 case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
5991 case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL:
5992 case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
5993 case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
5994 case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
5995 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
5996 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
5997 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
5998 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
5999 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX:
6000 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN:
6001 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAXIMUM:
6002 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMINIMUM:
6003 Res = WidenVecOp_VECREDUCE(N);
6004 break;
6005 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FADD:
6006 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FMUL:
6007 Res = WidenVecOp_VECREDUCE_SEQ(N);
6008 break;
6009 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FADD:
6010 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SEQ_FADD:
6011 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMUL:
6012 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SEQ_FMUL:
6013 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_ADD:
6014 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_MUL:
6015 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_AND:
6016 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_OR:
6017 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_XOR:
6018 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMAX:
6019 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMIN:
6020 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMAX:
6021 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMIN:
6022 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMAX:
6023 case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMIN:
6024 Res = WidenVecOp_VP_REDUCE(N);
6025 break;
6026 }
6027
6028 // If Res is null, the sub-method took care of registering the result.
6029 if (!Res.getNode()) return false;
6030
6031 // If the result is N, the sub-method updated N in place. Tell the legalizer
6032 // core about this.
6033 if (Res.getNode() == N)
6034 return true;
6035
6036
6037 if (N->isStrictFPOpcode())
6038 assert(Res.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) && N->getNumValues() == 2 &&
6039 "Invalid operand expansion");
6040 else
6041 assert(Res.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) && N->getNumValues() == 1 &&
6042 "Invalid operand expansion");
6043
6044 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res);
6045 return false;
6046}
6047
6048SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_EXTEND(SDNode *N) {
6049 SDLoc DL(N);
6050 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6051
6052 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(0);
6053 assert(getTypeAction(InOp.getValueType()) ==
6054 TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
6055 "Unexpected type action");
6056 InOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
6057 assert(VT.getVectorNumElements() <
6058 InOp.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() &&
6059 "Input wasn't widened!");
6060
6061 // We may need to further widen the operand until it has the same total
6062 // vector size as the result.
6063 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
6064 if (InVT.getSizeInBits() != VT.getSizeInBits()) {
6065 EVT InEltVT = InVT.getVectorElementType();
6066 for (EVT FixedVT : MVT::vector_valuetypes()) {
6067 EVT FixedEltVT = FixedVT.getVectorElementType();
6068 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(FixedVT) &&
6069 FixedVT.getSizeInBits() == VT.getSizeInBits() &&
6070 FixedEltVT == InEltVT) {
6071 assert(FixedVT.getVectorNumElements() >= VT.getVectorNumElements() &&
6072 "Not enough elements in the fixed type for the operand!");
6073 assert(FixedVT.getVectorNumElements() != InVT.getVectorNumElements() &&
6074 "We can't have the same type as we started with!");
6075 if (FixedVT.getVectorNumElements() > InVT.getVectorNumElements())
6076 InOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, FixedVT,
6077 DAG.getUNDEF(FixedVT), InOp,
6078 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
6079 else
6080 InOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, FixedVT, InOp,
6081 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
6082 break;
6083 }
6084 }
6085 InVT = InOp.getValueType();
6086 if (InVT.getSizeInBits() != VT.getSizeInBits())
6087 // We couldn't find a legal vector type that was a widening of the input
6088 // and could be extended in-register to the result type, so we have to
6089 // scalarize.
6090 return WidenVecOp_Convert(N);
6091 }
6092
6093 // Use special DAG nodes to represent the operation of extending the
6094 // low lanes.
6095 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
6096 default:
6097 llvm_unreachable("Extend legalization on extend operation!");
6098 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
6099 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, DL, VT, InOp);
6100 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
6101 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, DL, VT, InOp);
6102 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
6103 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, DL, VT, InOp);
6104 }
6105}
6106
6107SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_UnrollVectorOp(SDNode *N) {
6108 // The result (and first input) is legal, but the second input is illegal.
6109 // We can't do much to fix that, so just unroll and let the extracts off of
6110 // the second input be widened as needed later.
6111 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(N);
6112}
6113
6114SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_IS_FPCLASS(SDNode *N) {
6115 SDLoc DL(N);
6116 EVT ResultVT = N->getValueType(0);
6117 SDValue Test = N->getOperand(1);
6118 SDValue WideArg = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6119
6120 // Process this node similarly to SETCC.
6121 EVT WideResultVT = getSetCCResultType(WideArg.getValueType());
6122 if (ResultVT.getScalarType() == MVT::i1)
6123 WideResultVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), MVT::i1,
6124 WideResultVT.getVectorNumElements());
6125
6126 SDValue WideNode = DAG.getNode(ISD::IS_FPCLASS, DL, WideResultVT,
6127 {WideArg, Test}, N->getFlags());
6128
6129 // Extract the needed results from the result vector.
6130 EVT ResVT =
6131 EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), WideResultVT.getVectorElementType(),
6132 ResultVT.getVectorNumElements());
6133 SDValue CC = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, ResVT, WideNode,
6134 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
6135
6136 EVT OpVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
6137 ISD::NodeType ExtendCode =
6138 TargetLowering::getExtendForContent(TLI.getBooleanContents(OpVT));
6139 return DAG.getNode(ExtendCode, DL, ResultVT, CC);
6140}
6141
6142SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_Convert(SDNode *N) {
6143 // Since the result is legal and the input is illegal.
6144 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6145 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
6146 SDLoc dl(N);
6147 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(N->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0);
6148 assert(getTypeAction(InOp.getValueType()) ==
6149 TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
6150 "Unexpected type action");
6151 InOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
6152 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
6153 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
6154
6155 // See if a widened result type would be legal, if so widen the node.
6156 // FIXME: This isn't safe for StrictFP. Other optimization here is needed.
6157 EVT WideVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), EltVT,
6158 InVT.getVectorElementCount());
6159 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(WideVT) && !N->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
6160 SDValue Res;
6161 if (N->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
6162 if (Opcode == ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND)
6163 Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, { WideVT, MVT::Other },
6164 { N->getOperand(0), InOp, N->getOperand(2) });
6165 else
6166 Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, { WideVT, MVT::Other },
6167 { N->getOperand(0), InOp });
6168 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
6169 // use the new one.
6170 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Res.getValue(1));
6171 } else {
6172 if (Opcode == ISD::FP_ROUND)
6173 Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, WideVT, InOp, N->getOperand(1));
6174 else
6175 Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, WideVT, InOp);
6176 }
6177 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, VT, Res,
6178 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
6179 }
6180
6181 EVT InEltVT = InVT.getVectorElementType();
6182
6183 // Unroll the convert into some scalar code and create a nasty build vector.
6184 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
6185 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(NumElts);
6186 if (N->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
6187 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> NewOps(N->op_begin(), N->op_end());
6188 SmallVector<SDValue, 32> OpChains;
6189 for (unsigned i=0; i < NumElts; ++i) {
6190 NewOps[1] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, InEltVT, InOp,
6191 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
6192 Ops[i] = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, { EltVT, MVT::Other }, NewOps);
6193 OpChains.push_back(Ops[i].getValue(1));
6194 }
6195 SDValue NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, OpChains);
6196 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), NewChain);
6197 } else {
6198 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElts; ++i)
6199 Ops[i] = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, EltVT,
6200 DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, InEltVT,
6201 InOp, DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl)));
6202 }
6203
6204 return DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, Ops);
6205}
6206
6207SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_FP_TO_XINT_SAT(SDNode *N) {
6208 EVT DstVT = N->getValueType(0);
6209 SDValue Src = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6210 EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
6211 ElementCount WideNumElts = SrcVT.getVectorElementCount();
6212 SDLoc dl(N);
6213
6214 // See if a widened result type would be legal, if so widen the node.
6215 EVT WideDstVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6216 DstVT.getVectorElementType(), WideNumElts);
6217 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(WideDstVT)) {
6218 SDValue Res =
6219 DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, WideDstVT, Src, N->getOperand(1));
6220 return DAG.getNode(
6221 ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, DstVT, Res,
6222 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
6223 }
6224
6225 // Give up and unroll.
6226 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(N);
6227}
6228
6229SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_BITCAST(SDNode *N) {
6230 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6231 SDValue InOp = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6232 EVT InWidenVT = InOp.getValueType();
6233 SDLoc dl(N);
6234
6235 // Check if we can convert between two legal vector types and extract.
6236 TypeSize InWidenSize = InWidenVT.getSizeInBits();
6237 TypeSize Size = VT.getSizeInBits();
6238 // x86mmx is not an acceptable vector element type, so don't try.
6239 if (!VT.isVector() && VT != MVT::x86mmx &&
6240 InWidenSize.hasKnownScalarFactor(Size)) {
6241 unsigned NewNumElts = InWidenSize.getKnownScalarFactor(Size);
6242 EVT NewVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), VT, NewNumElts);
6243 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(NewVT)) {
6244 SDValue BitOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVT, InOp);
6245 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, VT, BitOp,
6246 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
6247 }
6248 }
6249
6250 // Handle a case like bitcast v12i8 -> v3i32. Normally that would get widened
6251 // to v16i8 -> v4i32, but for a target where v3i32 is legal but v12i8 is not,
6252 // we end up here. Handling the case here with EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR avoids
6253 // having to copy via memory.
6254 if (VT.isVector()) {
6255 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
6256 unsigned EltSize = EltVT.getFixedSizeInBits();
6257 if (InWidenSize.isKnownMultipleOf(EltSize)) {
6258 ElementCount NewNumElts =
6259 (InWidenVT.getVectorElementCount() * InWidenVT.getScalarSizeInBits())
6260 .divideCoefficientBy(EltSize);
6261 EVT NewVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), EltVT, NewNumElts);
6262 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(NewVT)) {
6263 SDValue BitOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVT, InOp);
6264 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, VT, BitOp,
6265 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
6266 }
6267 }
6268 }
6269
6270 return CreateStackStoreLoad(InOp, VT);
6271}
6272
6273SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_CONCAT_VECTORS(SDNode *N) {
6274 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6275 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
6276 EVT InVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
6277 SDLoc dl(N);
6278
6279 // If the widen width for this operand is the same as the width of the concat
6280 // and all but the first operand is undef, just use the widened operand.
6281 unsigned NumOperands = N->getNumOperands();
6282 if (VT == TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), InVT)) {
6283 unsigned i;
6284 for (i = 1; i < NumOperands; ++i)
6285 if (!N->getOperand(i).isUndef())
6286 break;
6287
6288 if (i == NumOperands)
6289 return GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6290 }
6291
6292 // Otherwise, fall back to a nasty build vector.
6293 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
6294 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(NumElts);
6295
6296 unsigned NumInElts = InVT.getVectorNumElements();
6297
6298 unsigned Idx = 0;
6299 for (unsigned i=0; i < NumOperands; ++i) {
6300 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(i);
6301 assert(getTypeAction(InOp.getValueType()) ==
6302 TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
6303 "Unexpected type action");
6304 InOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
6305 for (unsigned j = 0; j < NumInElts; ++j)
6306 Ops[Idx++] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT, InOp,
6307 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(j, dl));
6308 }
6309 return DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, Ops);
6310}
6311
6312SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_INSERT_SUBVECTOR(SDNode *N) {
6313 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6314 SDValue SubVec = N->getOperand(1);
6315 SDValue InVec = N->getOperand(0);
6316
6317 if (getTypeAction(SubVec.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector)
6318 SubVec = GetWidenedVector(SubVec);
6319
6320 if (SubVec.getValueType().knownBitsLE(VT) && InVec.isUndef() &&
6321 N->getConstantOperandVal(2) == 0)
6322 return DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, SDLoc(N), VT, InVec, SubVec,
6323 N->getOperand(2));
6324
6325 report_fatal_error("Don't know how to widen the operands for "
6326 "INSERT_SUBVECTOR");
6327}
6328
6329SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(SDNode *N) {
6330 SDValue InOp = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6331 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, SDLoc(N),
6332 N->getValueType(0), InOp, N->getOperand(1));
6333}
6334
6335SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(SDNode *N) {
6336 SDValue InOp = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6337 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SDLoc(N),
6338 N->getValueType(0), InOp, N->getOperand(1));
6339}
6340
6341SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_STORE(SDNode *N) {
6342 // We have to widen the value, but we want only to store the original
6343 // vector type.
6344 StoreSDNode *ST = cast<StoreSDNode>(N);
6345
6346 if (!ST->getMemoryVT().getScalarType().isByteSized())
6347 return TLI.scalarizeVectorStore(ST, DAG);
6348
6349 if (ST->isTruncatingStore())
6350 return TLI.scalarizeVectorStore(ST, DAG);
6351
6352 // Generate a vector-predicated store if it is custom/legal on the target.
6353 // To avoid possible recursion, only do this if the widened mask type is
6354 // legal.
6355 // FIXME: Not all targets may support EVL in VP_STORE. These will have been
6356 // removed from the IR by the ExpandVectorPredication pass but we're
6357 // reintroducing them here.
6358 SDValue StVal = ST->getValue();
6359 EVT StVT = StVal.getValueType();
6360 EVT WideVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), StVT);
6361 EVT WideMaskVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), MVT::i1,
6362 WideVT.getVectorElementCount());
6363
6364 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::VP_STORE, WideVT) &&
6365 TLI.isTypeLegal(WideMaskVT)) {
6366 // Widen the value.
6367 SDLoc DL(N);
6368 StVal = GetWidenedVector(StVal);
6369 SDValue Mask = DAG.getAllOnesConstant(DL, WideMaskVT);
6370 SDValue EVL = DAG.getElementCount(DL, TLI.getVPExplicitVectorLengthTy(),
6371 StVT.getVectorElementCount());
6372 return DAG.getStoreVP(ST->getChain(), DL, StVal, ST->getBasePtr(),
6373 DAG.getUNDEF(ST->getBasePtr().getValueType()), Mask,
6374 EVL, StVT, ST->getMemOperand(),
6375 ST->getAddressingMode());
6376 }
6377
6378 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> StChain;
6379 if (GenWidenVectorStores(StChain, ST)) {
6380 if (StChain.size() == 1)
6381 return StChain[0];
6382
6383 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SDLoc(ST), MVT::Other, StChain);
6384 }
6385
6386 report_fatal_error("Unable to widen vector store");
6387}
6388
6389SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VP_STORE(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
6390 assert((OpNo == 1 || OpNo == 3) &&
6391 "Can widen only data or mask operand of vp_store");
6392 VPStoreSDNode *ST = cast<VPStoreSDNode>(N);
6393 SDValue Mask = ST->getMask();
6394 SDValue StVal = ST->getValue();
6395 SDLoc dl(N);
6396
6397 if (OpNo == 1) {
6398 // Widen the value.
6399 StVal = GetWidenedVector(StVal);
6400
6401 // We only handle the case where the mask needs widening to an
6402 // identically-sized type as the vector inputs.
6403 assert(getTypeAction(Mask.getValueType()) ==
6404 TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
6405 "Unable to widen VP store");
6406 Mask = GetWidenedVector(Mask);
6407 } else {
6408 Mask = GetWidenedVector(Mask);
6409
6410 // We only handle the case where the stored value needs widening to an
6411 // identically-sized type as the mask.
6412 assert(getTypeAction(StVal.getValueType()) ==
6413 TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
6414 "Unable to widen VP store");
6415 StVal = GetWidenedVector(StVal);
6416 }
6417
6418 assert(Mask.getValueType().getVectorElementCount() ==
6419 StVal.getValueType().getVectorElementCount() &&
6420 "Mask and data vectors should have the same number of elements");
6421 return DAG.getStoreVP(ST->getChain(), dl, StVal, ST->getBasePtr(),
6422 ST->getOffset(), Mask, ST->getVectorLength(),
6423 ST->getMemoryVT(), ST->getMemOperand(),
6424 ST->getAddressingMode(), ST->isTruncatingStore(),
6425 ST->isCompressingStore());
6426}
6427
6428SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VP_STRIDED_STORE(SDNode *N,
6429 unsigned OpNo) {
6430 assert((OpNo == 1 || OpNo == 4) &&
6431 "Can widen only data or mask operand of vp_strided_store");
6432 VPStridedStoreSDNode *SST = cast<VPStridedStoreSDNode>(N);
6433 SDValue Mask = SST->getMask();
6434 SDValue StVal = SST->getValue();
6435 SDLoc DL(N);
6436
6437 if (OpNo == 1)
6438 assert(getTypeAction(Mask.getValueType()) ==
6439 TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
6440 "Unable to widen VP strided store");
6441 else
6442 assert(getTypeAction(StVal.getValueType()) ==
6443 TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
6444 "Unable to widen VP strided store");
6445
6446 StVal = GetWidenedVector(StVal);
6447 Mask = GetWidenedVector(Mask);
6448
6449 assert(StVal.getValueType().getVectorElementCount() ==
6450 Mask.getValueType().getVectorElementCount() &&
6451 "Data and mask vectors should have the same number of elements");
6452
6453 return DAG.getStridedStoreVP(
6454 SST->getChain(), DL, StVal, SST->getBasePtr(), SST->getOffset(),
6455 SST->getStride(), Mask, SST->getVectorLength(), SST->getMemoryVT(),
6456 SST->getMemOperand(), SST->getAddressingMode(), SST->isTruncatingStore(),
6457 SST->isCompressingStore());
6458}
6459
6460SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_MSTORE(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
6461 assert((OpNo == 1 || OpNo == 3) &&
6462 "Can widen only data or mask operand of mstore");
6463 MaskedStoreSDNode *MST = cast<MaskedStoreSDNode>(N);
6464 SDValue Mask = MST->getMask();
6465 EVT MaskVT = Mask.getValueType();
6466 SDValue StVal = MST->getValue();
6467 SDLoc dl(N);
6468
6469 if (OpNo == 1) {
6470 // Widen the value.
6471 StVal = GetWidenedVector(StVal);
6472
6473 // The mask should be widened as well.
6474 EVT WideVT = StVal.getValueType();
6475 EVT WideMaskVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6476 MaskVT.getVectorElementType(),
6477 WideVT.getVectorNumElements());
6478 Mask = ModifyToType(Mask, WideMaskVT, true);
6479 } else {
6480 // Widen the mask.
6481 EVT WideMaskVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), MaskVT);
6482 Mask = ModifyToType(Mask, WideMaskVT, true);
6483
6484 EVT ValueVT = StVal.getValueType();
6485 EVT WideVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6486 ValueVT.getVectorElementType(),
6487 WideMaskVT.getVectorNumElements());
6488 StVal = ModifyToType(StVal, WideVT);
6489 }
6490
6491 assert(Mask.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() ==
6492 StVal.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() &&
6493 "Mask and data vectors should have the same number of elements");
6494 return DAG.getMaskedStore(MST->getChain(), dl, StVal, MST->getBasePtr(),
6495 MST->getOffset(), Mask, MST->getMemoryVT(),
6496 MST->getMemOperand(), MST->getAddressingMode(),
6497 false, MST->isCompressingStore());
6498}
6499
6500SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_MGATHER(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
6501 assert(OpNo == 4 && "Can widen only the index of mgather");
6502 auto *MG = cast<MaskedGatherSDNode>(N);
6503 SDValue DataOp = MG->getPassThru();
6504 SDValue Mask = MG->getMask();
6505 SDValue Scale = MG->getScale();
6506
6507 // Just widen the index. It's allowed to have extra elements.
6508 SDValue Index = GetWidenedVector(MG->getIndex());
6509
6510 SDLoc dl(N);
6511 SDValue Ops[] = {MG->getChain(), DataOp, Mask, MG->getBasePtr(), Index,
6512 Scale};
6513 SDValue Res = DAG.getMaskedGather(MG->getVTList(), MG->getMemoryVT(), dl, Ops,
6514 MG->getMemOperand(), MG->getIndexType(),
6515 MG->getExtensionType());
6516 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Res.getValue(1));
6517 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res.getValue(0));
6518 return SDValue();
6519}
6520
6521SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_MSCATTER(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
6522 MaskedScatterSDNode *MSC = cast<MaskedScatterSDNode>(N);
6523 SDValue DataOp = MSC->getValue();
6524 SDValue Mask = MSC->getMask();
6525 SDValue Index = MSC->getIndex();
6526 SDValue Scale = MSC->getScale();
6527 EVT WideMemVT = MSC->getMemoryVT();
6528
6529 if (OpNo == 1) {
6530 DataOp = GetWidenedVector(DataOp);
6531 unsigned NumElts = DataOp.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
6532
6533 // Widen index.
6534 EVT IndexVT = Index.getValueType();
6535 EVT WideIndexVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6536 IndexVT.getVectorElementType(), NumElts);
6537 Index = ModifyToType(Index, WideIndexVT);
6538
6539 // The mask should be widened as well.
6540 EVT MaskVT = Mask.getValueType();
6541 EVT WideMaskVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6542 MaskVT.getVectorElementType(), NumElts);
6543 Mask = ModifyToType(Mask, WideMaskVT, true);
6544
6545 // Widen the MemoryType
6546 WideMemVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6547 MSC->getMemoryVT().getScalarType(), NumElts);
6548 } else if (OpNo == 4) {
6549 // Just widen the index. It's allowed to have extra elements.
6550 Index = GetWidenedVector(Index);
6551 } else
6552 llvm_unreachable("Can't widen this operand of mscatter");
6553
6554 SDValue Ops[] = {MSC->getChain(), DataOp, Mask, MSC->getBasePtr(), Index,
6555 Scale};
6556 return DAG.getMaskedScatter(DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other), WideMemVT, SDLoc(N),
6557 Ops, MSC->getMemOperand(), MSC->getIndexType(),
6558 MSC->isTruncatingStore());
6559}
6560
6561SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VP_SCATTER(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
6562 VPScatterSDNode *VPSC = cast<VPScatterSDNode>(N);
6563 SDValue DataOp = VPSC->getValue();
6564 SDValue Mask = VPSC->getMask();
6565 SDValue Index = VPSC->getIndex();
6566 SDValue Scale = VPSC->getScale();
6567 EVT WideMemVT = VPSC->getMemoryVT();
6568
6569 if (OpNo == 1) {
6570 DataOp = GetWidenedVector(DataOp);
6571 Index = GetWidenedVector(Index);
6572 const auto WideEC = DataOp.getValueType().getVectorElementCount();
6573 Mask = GetWidenedMask(Mask, WideEC);
6574 WideMemVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6575 VPSC->getMemoryVT().getScalarType(), WideEC);
6576 } else if (OpNo == 3) {
6577 // Just widen the index. It's allowed to have extra elements.
6578 Index = GetWidenedVector(Index);
6579 } else
6580 llvm_unreachable("Can't widen this operand of VP_SCATTER");
6581
6582 SDValue Ops[] = {
6583 VPSC->getChain(), DataOp, VPSC->getBasePtr(), Index, Scale, Mask,
6584 VPSC->getVectorLength()};
6585 return DAG.getScatterVP(DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other), WideMemVT, SDLoc(N), Ops,
6586 VPSC->getMemOperand(), VPSC->getIndexType());
6587}
6588
6589SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_SETCC(SDNode *N) {
6590 SDValue InOp0 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6591 SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
6592 SDLoc dl(N);
6593 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6594
6595 // WARNING: In this code we widen the compare instruction with garbage.
6596 // This garbage may contain denormal floats which may be slow. Is this a real
6597 // concern ? Should we zero the unused lanes if this is a float compare ?
6598
6599 // Get a new SETCC node to compare the newly widened operands.
6600 // Only some of the compared elements are legal.
6601 EVT SVT = getSetCCResultType(InOp0.getValueType());
6602 // The result type is legal, if its vXi1, keep vXi1 for the new SETCC.
6603 if (VT.getScalarType() == MVT::i1)
6604 SVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), MVT::i1,
6605 SVT.getVectorElementCount());
6606
6607 SDValue WideSETCC = DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, SDLoc(N),
6608 SVT, InOp0, InOp1, N->getOperand(2));
6609
6610 // Extract the needed results from the result vector.
6611 EVT ResVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
6612 SVT.getVectorElementType(),
6613 VT.getVectorElementCount());
6614 SDValue CC = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, ResVT, WideSETCC,
6615 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
6616
6617 EVT OpVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
6618 ISD::NodeType ExtendCode =
6619 TargetLowering::getExtendForContent(TLI.getBooleanContents(OpVT));
6620 return DAG.getNode(ExtendCode, dl, VT, CC);
6621}
6622
6623SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_STRICT_FSETCC(SDNode *N) {
6624 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
6625 SDValue LHS = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
6626 SDValue RHS = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(2));
6627 SDValue CC = N->getOperand(3);
6628 SDLoc dl(N);
6629
6630 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6631 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
6632 EVT TmpEltVT = LHS.getValueType().getVectorElementType();
6633 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
6634
6635 // Unroll into a build vector.
6636 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Scalars(NumElts);
6637 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Chains(NumElts);
6638
6639 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
6640 SDValue LHSElem = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, TmpEltVT, LHS,
6641 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
6642 SDValue RHSElem = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, TmpEltVT, RHS,
6643 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
6644
6645 Scalars[i] = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, {MVT::i1, MVT::Other},
6646 {Chain, LHSElem, RHSElem, CC});
6647 Chains[i] = Scalars[i].getValue(1);
6648 Scalars[i] = DAG.getSelect(dl, EltVT, Scalars[i],
6649 DAG.getBoolConstant(true, dl, EltVT, VT),
6650 DAG.getBoolConstant(false, dl, EltVT, VT));
6651 }
6652
6653 SDValue NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Chains);
6654 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), NewChain);
6655
6656 return DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, Scalars);
6657}
6658
6659SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VECREDUCE(SDNode *N) {
6660 SDLoc dl(N);
6661 SDValue Op = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6662 EVT OrigVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
6663 EVT WideVT = Op.getValueType();
6664 EVT ElemVT = OrigVT.getVectorElementType();
6665 SDNodeFlags Flags = N->getFlags();
6666
6667 unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode();
6668 unsigned BaseOpc = ISD::getVecReduceBaseOpcode(Opc);
6669 SDValue NeutralElem = DAG.getNeutralElement(BaseOpc, dl, ElemVT, Flags);
6670 assert(NeutralElem && "Neutral element must exist");
6671
6672 // Pad the vector with the neutral element.
6673 unsigned OrigElts = OrigVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
6674 unsigned WideElts = WideVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
6675
6676 if (WideVT.isScalableVector()) {
6677 unsigned GCD = std::gcd(OrigElts, WideElts);
6678 EVT SplatVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), ElemVT,
6679 ElementCount::getScalable(GCD));
6680 SDValue SplatNeutral = DAG.getSplatVector(SplatVT, dl, NeutralElem);
6681 for (unsigned Idx = OrigElts; Idx < WideElts; Idx = Idx + GCD)
6682 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, dl, WideVT, Op, SplatNeutral,
6683 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
6684 return DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, N->getValueType(0), Op, Flags);
6685 }
6686
6687 for (unsigned Idx = OrigElts; Idx < WideElts; Idx++)
6688 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, WideVT, Op, NeutralElem,
6689 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
6690
6691 return DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, N->getValueType(0), Op, Flags);
6692}
6693
6694SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VECREDUCE_SEQ(SDNode *N) {
6695 SDLoc dl(N);
6696 SDValue AccOp = N->getOperand(0);
6697 SDValue VecOp = N->getOperand(1);
6698 SDValue Op = GetWidenedVector(VecOp);
6699
6700 EVT OrigVT = VecOp.getValueType();
6701 EVT WideVT = Op.getValueType();
6702 EVT ElemVT = OrigVT.getVectorElementType();
6703 SDNodeFlags Flags = N->getFlags();
6704
6705 unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode();
6706 unsigned BaseOpc = ISD::getVecReduceBaseOpcode(Opc);
6707 SDValue NeutralElem = DAG.getNeutralElement(BaseOpc, dl, ElemVT, Flags);
6708
6709 // Pad the vector with the neutral element.
6710 unsigned OrigElts = OrigVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
6711 unsigned WideElts = WideVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
6712
6713 if (WideVT.isScalableVector()) {
6714 unsigned GCD = std::gcd(OrigElts, WideElts);
6715 EVT SplatVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), ElemVT,
6716 ElementCount::getScalable(GCD));
6717 SDValue SplatNeutral = DAG.getSplatVector(SplatVT, dl, NeutralElem);
6718 for (unsigned Idx = OrigElts; Idx < WideElts; Idx = Idx + GCD)
6719 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, dl, WideVT, Op, SplatNeutral,
6720 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
6721 return DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, N->getValueType(0), AccOp, Op, Flags);
6722 }
6723
6724 for (unsigned Idx = OrigElts; Idx < WideElts; Idx++)
6725 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, WideVT, Op, NeutralElem,
6726 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
6727
6728 return DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, N->getValueType(0), AccOp, Op, Flags);
6729}
6730
6731SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VP_REDUCE(SDNode *N) {
6732 assert(N->isVPOpcode() && "Expected VP opcode");
6733
6734 SDLoc dl(N);
6735 SDValue Op = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
6736 SDValue Mask = GetWidenedMask(N->getOperand(2),
6737 Op.getValueType().getVectorElementCount());
6738
6739 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, N->getValueType(0),
6740 {N->getOperand(0), Op, Mask, N->getOperand(3)},
6741 N->getFlags());
6742}
6743
6744SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VSELECT(SDNode *N) {
6745 // This only gets called in the case that the left and right inputs and
6746 // result are of a legal odd vector type, and the condition is illegal i1 of
6747 // the same odd width that needs widening.
6748 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
6749 assert(VT.isVector() && !VT.isPow2VectorType() && isTypeLegal(VT));
6750
6751 SDValue Cond = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
6752 SDValue LeftIn = DAG.WidenVector(N->getOperand(1), SDLoc(N));
6753 SDValue RightIn = DAG.WidenVector(N->getOperand(2), SDLoc(N));
6754 SDLoc DL(N);
6755
6756 SDValue Select = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, LeftIn.getValueType(), Cond,
6757 LeftIn, RightIn);
6758 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VT, Select,
6759 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
6760}
6761
6762//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6763// Vector Widening Utilities
6764//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6765
6766// Utility function to find the type to chop up a widen vector for load/store
6767// TLI: Target lowering used to determine legal types.
6768// Width: Width left need to load/store.
6769// WidenVT: The widen vector type to load to/store from
6770// Align: If 0, don't allow use of a wider type
6771// WidenEx: If Align is not 0, the amount additional we can load/store from.
6772
6773static std::optional<EVT> findMemType(SelectionDAG &DAG,
6774 const TargetLowering &TLI, unsigned Width,
6775 EVT WidenVT, unsigned Align = 0,
6776 unsigned WidenEx = 0) {
6777 EVT WidenEltVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
6778 const bool Scalable = WidenVT.isScalableVector();
6779 unsigned WidenWidth = WidenVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
6780 unsigned WidenEltWidth = WidenEltVT.getSizeInBits();
6781 unsigned AlignInBits = Align*8;
6782
6783 // If we have one element to load/store, return it.
6784 EVT RetVT = WidenEltVT;
6785 if (!Scalable && Width == WidenEltWidth)
6786 return RetVT;
6787
6788 // Don't bother looking for an integer type if the vector is scalable, skip
6789 // to vector types.
6790 if (!Scalable) {
6791 // See if there is larger legal integer than the element type to load/store.
6792 for (EVT MemVT : reverse(MVT::integer_valuetypes())) {
6793 unsigned MemVTWidth = MemVT.getSizeInBits();
6794 if (MemVT.getSizeInBits() <= WidenEltWidth)
6795 break;
6796 auto Action = TLI.getTypeAction(*DAG.getContext(), MemVT);
6797 if ((Action == TargetLowering::TypeLegal ||
6798 Action == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger) &&
6799 (WidenWidth % MemVTWidth) == 0 &&
6800 isPowerOf2_32(WidenWidth / MemVTWidth) &&
6801 (MemVTWidth <= Width ||
6802 (Align!=0 && MemVTWidth<=AlignInBits && MemVTWidth<=Width+WidenEx))) {
6803 if (MemVTWidth == WidenWidth)
6804 return MemVT;
6805 RetVT = MemVT;
6806 break;
6807 }
6808 }
6809 }
6810
6811 // See if there is a larger vector type to load/store that has the same vector
6812 // element type and is evenly divisible with the WidenVT.
6813 for (EVT MemVT : reverse(MVT::vector_valuetypes())) {
6814 // Skip vector MVTs which don't match the scalable property of WidenVT.
6815 if (Scalable != MemVT.isScalableVector())
6816 continue;
6817 unsigned MemVTWidth = MemVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
6818 auto Action = TLI.getTypeAction(*DAG.getContext(), MemVT);
6819 if ((Action == TargetLowering::TypeLegal ||
6820 Action == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger) &&
6821 WidenEltVT == MemVT.getVectorElementType() &&
6822 (WidenWidth % MemVTWidth) == 0 &&
6823 isPowerOf2_32(WidenWidth / MemVTWidth) &&
6824 (MemVTWidth <= Width ||
6825 (Align!=0 && MemVTWidth<=AlignInBits && MemVTWidth<=Width+WidenEx))) {
6826 if (RetVT.getFixedSizeInBits() < MemVTWidth || MemVT == WidenVT)
6827 return MemVT;
6828 }
6829 }
6830
6831 // Using element-wise loads and stores for widening operations is not
6832 // supported for scalable vectors
6833 if (Scalable)
6834 return std::nullopt;
6835
6836 return RetVT;
6837}
6838
6839// Builds a vector type from scalar loads
6840// VecTy: Resulting Vector type
6841// LDOps: Load operators to build a vector type
6842// [Start,End) the list of loads to use.
6843static SDValue BuildVectorFromScalar(SelectionDAG& DAG, EVT VecTy,
6844 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &LdOps,
6845 unsigned Start, unsigned End) {
6846 SDLoc dl(LdOps[Start]);
6847 EVT LdTy = LdOps[Start].getValueType();
6848 unsigned Width = VecTy.getSizeInBits();
6849 unsigned NumElts = Width / LdTy.getSizeInBits();
6850 EVT NewVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), LdTy, NumElts);
6851
6852 unsigned Idx = 1;
6853 SDValue VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, NewVecVT,LdOps[Start]);
6854
6855 for (unsigned i = Start + 1; i != End; ++i) {
6856 EVT NewLdTy = LdOps[i].getValueType();
6857 if (NewLdTy != LdTy) {
6858 NumElts = Width / NewLdTy.getSizeInBits();
6859 NewVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), NewLdTy, NumElts);
6860 VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVecVT, VecOp);
6861 // Readjust position and vector position based on new load type.
6862 Idx = Idx * LdTy.getSizeInBits() / NewLdTy.getSizeInBits();
6863 LdTy = NewLdTy;
6864 }
6865 VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, NewVecVT, VecOp, LdOps[i],
6866 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx++, dl));
6867 }
6868 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VecTy, VecOp);
6869}
6870
6871SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::GenWidenVectorLoads(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &LdChain,
6872 LoadSDNode *LD) {
6873 // The strategy assumes that we can efficiently load power-of-two widths.
6874 // The routine chops the vector into the largest vector loads with the same
6875 // element type or scalar loads and then recombines it to the widen vector
6876 // type.
6877 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(),LD->getValueType(0));
6878 EVT LdVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
6879 SDLoc dl(LD);
6880 assert(LdVT.isVector() && WidenVT.isVector());
6881 assert(LdVT.isScalableVector() == WidenVT.isScalableVector());
6882 assert(LdVT.getVectorElementType() == WidenVT.getVectorElementType());
6883
6884 // Load information
6885 SDValue Chain = LD->getChain();
6886 SDValue BasePtr = LD->getBasePtr();
6887 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
6888 AAMDNodes AAInfo = LD->getAAInfo();
6889
6890 TypeSize LdWidth = LdVT.getSizeInBits();
6891 TypeSize WidenWidth = WidenVT.getSizeInBits();
6892 TypeSize WidthDiff = WidenWidth - LdWidth;
6893 // Allow wider loads if they are sufficiently aligned to avoid memory faults
6894 // and if the original load is simple.
6895 unsigned LdAlign =
6896 (!LD->isSimple() || LdVT.isScalableVector()) ? 0 : LD->getAlign().value();
6897
6898 // Find the vector type that can load from.
6899 std::optional<EVT> FirstVT =
6900 findMemType(DAG, TLI, LdWidth.getKnownMinValue(), WidenVT, LdAlign,
6901 WidthDiff.getKnownMinValue());
6902
6903 if (!FirstVT)
6904 return SDValue();
6905
6906 SmallVector<EVT, 8> MemVTs;
6907 TypeSize FirstVTWidth = FirstVT->getSizeInBits();
6908
6909 // Unless we're able to load in one instruction we must work out how to load
6910 // the remainder.
6911 if (!TypeSize::isKnownLE(LdWidth, FirstVTWidth)) {
6912 std::optional<EVT> NewVT = FirstVT;
6913 TypeSize RemainingWidth = LdWidth;
6914 TypeSize NewVTWidth = FirstVTWidth;
6915 do {
6916 RemainingWidth -= NewVTWidth;
6917 if (TypeSize::isKnownLT(RemainingWidth, NewVTWidth)) {
6918 // The current type we are using is too large. Find a better size.
6919 NewVT = findMemType(DAG, TLI, RemainingWidth.getKnownMinValue(),
6920 WidenVT, LdAlign, WidthDiff.getKnownMinValue());
6921 if (!NewVT)
6922 return SDValue();
6923 NewVTWidth = NewVT->getSizeInBits();
6924 }
6925 MemVTs.push_back(*NewVT);
6926 } while (TypeSize::isKnownGT(RemainingWidth, NewVTWidth));
6927 }
6928
6929 SDValue LdOp = DAG.getLoad(*FirstVT, dl, Chain, BasePtr, LD->getPointerInfo(),
6930 LD->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
6931 LdChain.push_back(LdOp.getValue(1));
6932
6933 // Check if we can load the element with one instruction.
6934 if (MemVTs.empty()) {
6935 assert(TypeSize::isKnownLE(LdWidth, FirstVTWidth));
6936 if (!FirstVT->isVector()) {
6937 unsigned NumElts =
6938 WidenWidth.getFixedValue() / FirstVTWidth.getFixedValue();
6939 EVT NewVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), *FirstVT, NumElts);
6940 SDValue VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, NewVecVT, LdOp);
6941 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, WidenVT, VecOp);
6942 }
6943 if (FirstVT == WidenVT)
6944 return LdOp;
6945
6946 // TODO: We don't currently have any tests that exercise this code path.
6947 assert(WidenWidth.getFixedValue() % FirstVTWidth.getFixedValue() == 0);
6948 unsigned NumConcat =
6949 WidenWidth.getFixedValue() / FirstVTWidth.getFixedValue();
6950 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> ConcatOps(NumConcat);
6951 SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(*FirstVT);
6952 ConcatOps[0] = LdOp;
6953 for (unsigned i = 1; i != NumConcat; ++i)
6954 ConcatOps[i] = UndefVal;
6955 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, WidenVT, ConcatOps);
6956 }
6957
6958 // Load vector by using multiple loads from largest vector to scalar.
6959 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> LdOps;
6960 LdOps.push_back(LdOp);
6961
6962 uint64_t ScaledOffset = 0;
6963 MachinePointerInfo MPI = LD->getPointerInfo();
6964
6965 // First incremement past the first load.
6966 IncrementPointer(cast<LoadSDNode>(LdOp), *FirstVT, MPI, BasePtr,
6967 &ScaledOffset);
6968
6969 for (EVT MemVT : MemVTs) {
6970 Align NewAlign = ScaledOffset == 0
6971 ? LD->getOriginalAlign()
6972 : commonAlignment(LD->getAlign(), ScaledOffset);
6973 SDValue L =
6974 DAG.getLoad(MemVT, dl, Chain, BasePtr, MPI, NewAlign, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
6975
6976 LdOps.push_back(L);
6977 LdChain.push_back(L.getValue(1));
6978 IncrementPointer(cast<LoadSDNode>(L), MemVT, MPI, BasePtr, &ScaledOffset);
6979 }
6980
6981 // Build the vector from the load operations.
6982 unsigned End = LdOps.size();
6983 if (!LdOps[0].getValueType().isVector())
6984 // All the loads are scalar loads.
6985 return BuildVectorFromScalar(DAG, WidenVT, LdOps, 0, End);
6986
6987 // If the load contains vectors, build the vector using concat vector.
6988 // All of the vectors used to load are power-of-2, and the scalar loads can be
6989 // combined to make a power-of-2 vector.
6990 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> ConcatOps(End);
6991 int i = End - 1;
6992 int Idx = End;
6993 EVT LdTy = LdOps[i].getValueType();
6994 // First, combine the scalar loads to a vector.
6995 if (!LdTy.isVector()) {
6996 for (--i; i >= 0; --i) {
6997 LdTy = LdOps[i].getValueType();
6998 if (LdTy.isVector())
6999 break;
7000 }
7001 ConcatOps[--Idx] = BuildVectorFromScalar(DAG, LdTy, LdOps, i + 1, End);
7002 }
7003
7004 ConcatOps[--Idx] = LdOps[i];
7005 for (--i; i >= 0; --i) {
7006 EVT NewLdTy = LdOps[i].getValueType();
7007 if (NewLdTy != LdTy) {
7008 // Create a larger vector.
7009 TypeSize LdTySize = LdTy.getSizeInBits();
7010 TypeSize NewLdTySize = NewLdTy.getSizeInBits();
7011 assert(NewLdTySize.isScalable() == LdTySize.isScalable() &&
7012 NewLdTySize.isKnownMultipleOf(LdTySize.getKnownMinValue()));
7013 unsigned NumOps =
7014 NewLdTySize.getKnownMinValue() / LdTySize.getKnownMinValue();
7015 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> WidenOps(NumOps);
7016 unsigned j = 0;
7017 for (; j != End-Idx; ++j)
7018 WidenOps[j] = ConcatOps[Idx+j];
7019 for (; j != NumOps; ++j)
7020 WidenOps[j] = DAG.getUNDEF(LdTy);
7021
7022 ConcatOps[End-1] = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, NewLdTy,
7023 WidenOps);
7024 Idx = End - 1;
7025 LdTy = NewLdTy;
7026 }
7027 ConcatOps[--Idx] = LdOps[i];
7028 }
7029
7030 if (WidenWidth == LdTy.getSizeInBits() * (End - Idx))
7031 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, WidenVT,
7032 ArrayRef(&ConcatOps[Idx], End - Idx));
7033
7034 // We need to fill the rest with undefs to build the vector.
7035 unsigned NumOps =
7036 WidenWidth.getKnownMinValue() / LdTy.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
7037 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> WidenOps(NumOps);
7038 SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(LdTy);
7039 {
7040 unsigned i = 0;
7041 for (; i != End-Idx; ++i)
7042 WidenOps[i] = ConcatOps[Idx+i];
7043 for (; i != NumOps; ++i)
7044 WidenOps[i] = UndefVal;
7045 }
7046 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, WidenVT, WidenOps);
7047}
7048
7049SDValue
7050DAGTypeLegalizer::GenWidenVectorExtLoads(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &LdChain,
7051 LoadSDNode *LD,
7052 ISD::LoadExtType ExtType) {
7053 // For extension loads, it may not be more efficient to chop up the vector
7054 // and then extend it. Instead, we unroll the load and build a new vector.
7055 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(),LD->getValueType(0));
7056 EVT LdVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
7057 SDLoc dl(LD);
7058 assert(LdVT.isVector() && WidenVT.isVector());
7059 assert(LdVT.isScalableVector() == WidenVT.isScalableVector());
7060
7061 // Load information
7062 SDValue Chain = LD->getChain();
7063 SDValue BasePtr = LD->getBasePtr();
7064 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
7065 AAMDNodes AAInfo = LD->getAAInfo();
7066
7067 if (LdVT.isScalableVector())
7068 report_fatal_error("Generating widen scalable extending vector loads is "
7069 "not yet supported");
7070
7071 EVT EltVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
7072 EVT LdEltVT = LdVT.getVectorElementType();
7073 unsigned NumElts = LdVT.getVectorNumElements();
7074
7075 // Load each element and widen.
7076 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
7077 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(WidenNumElts);
7078 unsigned Increment = LdEltVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
7079 Ops[0] =
7080 DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, dl, EltVT, Chain, BasePtr, LD->getPointerInfo(),
7081 LdEltVT, LD->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
7082 LdChain.push_back(Ops[0].getValue(1));
7083 unsigned i = 0, Offset = Increment;
7084 for (i=1; i < NumElts; ++i, Offset += Increment) {
7085 SDValue NewBasePtr =
7086 DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, BasePtr, TypeSize::Fixed(Offset));
7087 Ops[i] = DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, dl, EltVT, Chain, NewBasePtr,
7088 LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset), LdEltVT,
7089 LD->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
7090 LdChain.push_back(Ops[i].getValue(1));
7091 }
7092
7093 // Fill the rest with undefs.
7094 SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT);
7095 for (; i != WidenNumElts; ++i)
7096 Ops[i] = UndefVal;
7097
7098 return DAG.getBuildVector(WidenVT, dl, Ops);
7099}
7100
7101bool DAGTypeLegalizer::GenWidenVectorStores(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &StChain,
7102 StoreSDNode *ST) {
7103 // The strategy assumes that we can efficiently store power-of-two widths.
7104 // The routine chops the vector into the largest vector stores with the same
7105 // element type or scalar stores.
7106 SDValue Chain = ST->getChain();
7107 SDValue BasePtr = ST->getBasePtr();
7108 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
7109 AAMDNodes AAInfo = ST->getAAInfo();
7110 SDValue ValOp = GetWidenedVector(ST->getValue());
7111 SDLoc dl(ST);
7112
7113 EVT StVT = ST->getMemoryVT();
7114 TypeSize StWidth = StVT.getSizeInBits();
7115 EVT ValVT = ValOp.getValueType();
7116 TypeSize ValWidth = ValVT.getSizeInBits();
7117 EVT ValEltVT = ValVT.getVectorElementType();
7118 unsigned ValEltWidth = ValEltVT.getFixedSizeInBits();
7119 assert(StVT.getVectorElementType() == ValEltVT);
7120 assert(StVT.isScalableVector() == ValVT.isScalableVector() &&
7121 "Mismatch between store and value types");
7122
7123 int Idx = 0; // current index to store
7124
7125 MachinePointerInfo MPI = ST->getPointerInfo();
7126 uint64_t ScaledOffset = 0;
7127
7128 // A breakdown of how to widen this vector store. Each element of the vector
7129 // is a memory VT combined with the number of times it is to be stored to,
7130 // e,g., v5i32 -> {{v2i32,2},{i32,1}}
7131 SmallVector<std::pair<EVT, unsigned>, 4> MemVTs;
7132
7133 while (StWidth.isNonZero()) {
7134 // Find the largest vector type we can store with.
7135 std::optional<EVT> NewVT =
7136 findMemType(DAG, TLI, StWidth.getKnownMinValue(), ValVT);
7137 if (!NewVT)
7138 return false;
7139 MemVTs.push_back({*NewVT, 0});
7140 TypeSize NewVTWidth = NewVT->getSizeInBits();
7141
7142 do {
7143 StWidth -= NewVTWidth;
7144 MemVTs.back().second++;
7145 } while (StWidth.isNonZero() && TypeSize::isKnownGE(StWidth, NewVTWidth));
7146 }
7147
7148 for (const auto &Pair : MemVTs) {
7149 EVT NewVT = Pair.first;
7150 unsigned Count = Pair.second;
7151 TypeSize NewVTWidth = NewVT.getSizeInBits();
7152
7153 if (NewVT.isVector()) {
7154 unsigned NumVTElts = NewVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
7155 do {
7156 Align NewAlign = ScaledOffset == 0
7157 ? ST->getOriginalAlign()
7158 : commonAlignment(ST->getAlign(), ScaledOffset);
7159 SDValue EOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, NewVT, ValOp,
7160 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
7161 SDValue PartStore = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, EOp, BasePtr, MPI, NewAlign,
7162 MMOFlags, AAInfo);
7163 StChain.push_back(PartStore);
7164
7165 Idx += NumVTElts;
7166 IncrementPointer(cast<StoreSDNode>(PartStore), NewVT, MPI, BasePtr,
7167 &ScaledOffset);
7168 } while (--Count);
7169 } else {
7170 // Cast the vector to the scalar type we can store.
7171 unsigned NumElts = ValWidth.getFixedValue() / NewVTWidth.getFixedValue();
7172 EVT NewVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), NewVT, NumElts);
7173 SDValue VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVecVT, ValOp);
7174 // Readjust index position based on new vector type.
7175 Idx = Idx * ValEltWidth / NewVTWidth.getFixedValue();
7176 do {
7177 SDValue EOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, NewVT, VecOp,
7178 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx++, dl));
7179 SDValue PartStore =
7180 DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, EOp, BasePtr, MPI, ST->getOriginalAlign(),
7181 MMOFlags, AAInfo);
7182 StChain.push_back(PartStore);
7183
7184 IncrementPointer(cast<StoreSDNode>(PartStore), NewVT, MPI, BasePtr);
7185 } while (--Count);
7186 // Restore index back to be relative to the original widen element type.
7187 Idx = Idx * NewVTWidth.getFixedValue() / ValEltWidth;
7188 }
7189 }
7190
7191 return true;
7192}
7193
7194/// Modifies a vector input (widen or narrows) to a vector of NVT. The
7195/// input vector must have the same element type as NVT.
7196/// FillWithZeroes specifies that the vector should be widened with zeroes.
7197SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ModifyToType(SDValue InOp, EVT NVT,
7198 bool FillWithZeroes) {
7199 // Note that InOp might have been widened so it might already have
7200 // the right width or it might need be narrowed.
7201 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
7202 assert(InVT.getVectorElementType() == NVT.getVectorElementType() &&
7203 "input and widen element type must match");
7204 assert(InVT.isScalableVector() == NVT.isScalableVector() &&
7205 "cannot modify scalable vectors in this way");
7206 SDLoc dl(InOp);
7207
7208 // Check if InOp already has the right width.
7209 if (InVT == NVT)
7210 return InOp;
7211
7212 ElementCount InEC = InVT.getVectorElementCount();
7213 ElementCount WidenEC = NVT.getVectorElementCount();
7214 if (WidenEC.hasKnownScalarFactor(InEC)) {
7215 unsigned NumConcat = WidenEC.getKnownScalarFactor(InEC);
7216 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(NumConcat);
7217 SDValue FillVal = FillWithZeroes ? DAG.getConstant(0, dl, InVT) :
7218 DAG.getUNDEF(InVT);
7219 Ops[0] = InOp;
7220 for (unsigned i = 1; i != NumConcat; ++i)
7221 Ops[i] = FillVal;
7222
7223 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, NVT, Ops);
7224 }
7225
7226 if (InEC.hasKnownScalarFactor(WidenEC))
7227 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, NVT, InOp,
7228 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
7229
7230 assert(!InVT.isScalableVector() && !NVT.isScalableVector() &&
7231 "Scalable vectors should have been handled already.");
7232
7233 unsigned InNumElts = InEC.getFixedValue();
7234 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenEC.getFixedValue();
7235
7236 // Fall back to extract and build (+ mask, if padding with zeros).
7237 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(WidenNumElts);
7238 EVT EltVT = NVT.getVectorElementType();
7239 unsigned MinNumElts = std::min(WidenNumElts, InNumElts);
7240 unsigned Idx;
7241 for (Idx = 0; Idx < MinNumElts; ++Idx)
7242 Ops[Idx] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT, InOp,
7243 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
7244
7245 SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT);
7246 for (; Idx < WidenNumElts; ++Idx)
7247 Ops[Idx] = UndefVal;
7248
7249 SDValue Widened = DAG.getBuildVector(NVT, dl, Ops);
7250 if (!FillWithZeroes)
7251 return Widened;
7252
7253 assert(NVT.isInteger() &&
7254 "We expect to never want to FillWithZeroes for non-integral types.");
7255
7256 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> MaskOps;
7257 MaskOps.append(MinNumElts, DAG.getAllOnesConstant(dl, EltVT));
7258 MaskOps.append(WidenNumElts - MinNumElts, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, EltVT));
7259
7260 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, NVT, Widened,
7261 DAG.getBuildVector(NVT, dl, MaskOps));
7262}
